Package: spaCraft
Title: spaCraft: Analysis-aware power calculation and
   sample size planning for multi-sample spatial transcriptomics
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jungmin", "Shin", email = "c16267@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Dongjun", "Chung", email = "chung.911@osu.edu",
           role = "aut"))
Author: Jungmin Shin [aut, cre],
  Dongjun Chung [aut]
Maintainer: Jungmin Shin <c16267@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a pilot-based framework for statistical power analysis and
    sample-size determination in comparative, multi-sample spatial
    transcriptomics studies. A cohort-level generative model is learned from
    pilot data through three layers: a baseline-anchored Binomial-logit model
    for domain composition, a Fisher-Gaussian kernel mixture model for spatial
    geometry (Mukhopadhyay, Li and Dunson (2020) <doi:10.1111/rssb.12390>), and
    a Gaussian-process expression model fitted with nearest-neighbor
    approximations (Saha and Datta (2018) <doi:10.1002/sta4.184>). Synthetic
    cohorts are generated under user-specified effect sizes, spatial domains are
    recovered with a pilot-guided extension of 'BANKSY' (Singhal et al. (2024)
    <doi:10.1038/s41588-024-01664-3>), and endpoint-specific power is estimated
    under a full generate-recover-test pipeline for a spatially adjusted
    differential-expression test and a baseline-anchored compositional test,
    both using a minimum-effect 'TREAT' margin (McCarthy and Smyth (2009)
    <doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/btp053>). Monte-Carlo power estimates are
    summarized with monotone shape-constrained additive models to recommend
    per-group sample sizes. The framework supports both replicated and
    single-pilot designs and has been evaluated across the 'Visium',
    'Visium HD', and 'Stereo-seq' platforms.
